author: Crowley, T. (2006). Naman: a vanishing language...
notes: Crowley, T. (2006). Naman: a vanishing language of Malakula (Vanuatu).  Edited by John Lynch. Pacific Linguistics. Research School of Pacific and Asian Studies. The Australian National University./kh/ = velar fricative, /ng/ = velar nasal, /ë/ = schwa
problems: Andreea: replaced /kh/ with velar fricative:-- voiced velar fricative intervocalically, word initially-- voiceless velar fricative word finally, or adjacent to unvoiced consonants(cf. Malcolm Ross)Also replaced ë with ə.
